Bianca Andreescu staged a dramatic comeback on Sunday to topple Garbine Muguruza in a battle of former Grand Slam champions on day one of the Adelaide International. The Canadian, who won the 2019 US Open, was crushed in the first set and slipped 2-5 behind in the second before surging home 0-6, 7-6 (7/3), 6-1 to get her 2023 season off to a winning start. It maintained her perfect record against two-time Grand Slam winner and former world No 1 Muguruza, improving to 3-0.